    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Variable reddish orange colors resembling the color of burnt ocher pigment, which is an iron oxide pigment prepared by burning yellow ocher or limonite.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000009521/Color: Universal Language and Dictionary (1976)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指色近於煅赭石顏料的各種紅橙色色彩，煅赭石是一種氧化鐵顏料，由燒炙黃赭石或褐鐵礦而得。

</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
